HERBARIUM
NCU
572107

Diapensiaceae *(handwritten)*

NORTH CAROLINA FLORA

Species *Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt
Date 15 November 2000 County Cumberland
Location South side of Lower Little River, west of north
end of Tissington Street, about 1.7 miles upstream
from Elliot Bridge. Coastal Plain physiographic
province.

Habitat Crest of steep slope along small blackwater
river. Locally common as scattered populations under
*Quercus nigra*, *Pinus taeda*, *Liquidambar styraciflua*,
*Chamaecyparis thyoides*, *Magnolia virginiana*,
*Symplocos tinctoria*, *Kalmia latifolia* (abundant), *Lyonia
lucida*.

B.A. Sorrie 10677
